        <presentation>
          <material>
            <mattext texttype="text/html">&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Read each scenario, then, using the verb in parentheses, write a simple &lt;strong&gt;&lt;i&gt;affirmative&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; or &lt;strong&gt;&lt;i&gt;negative&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; command that you would give to the following people. Follow the model given. Copy and paste these special characters whenever you need them for your answers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div style="border: 1px solid black; display: flex; justify-content: center; width: 20%; text-align: center; padding: 1%;"&gt;é &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; è&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Modèle:&lt;br&gt;YOU READ: You and your friends need to do more physical activity. (faire de l’exercice)&lt;br&gt;YOU WRITE: Faisons de l’exercice !&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;1. Your older brother is about to sneeze into your cake batter. (ne pas éternuer)&lt;br&gt;[RESPONSE]ici !&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;2. Your best friend is also about to cough into your batter. (ne pas tousser)&lt;br&gt;[RESPONSE1]ici !&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;3. You think they are both sick and both need to go see a doctor. (prendre rendez-vous)&lt;br&gt;[RESPONSE2]chez le médecin !&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;4. They have the flu. You think they both need to drink a lot of water to avoid dehydration. (rester hydratés)&lt;br&gt;Voilà deux verres d’eau. [RESPONSE3] !&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;5. They are tired and you are too from caring for them. All three of you need to get good sleep. (essayer de dormir)&lt;br&gt;[RESPONSE4]assez !&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</mattext>
